External styles: are defined within the <link> element, inside the <head> section of an HTML page;

Internal styles: are defined within the <style> element, inside the <head> section of an HTML page;

Inline styles: are defined within the "style" attribute of the relevant element: <h1 style="color:blue;text-align:center;">This is a heading</h1>


Background colorï¼š
	+ background-color:
	  opacity: 0.3  (1.0~0.0)
	+ background-image: url("paper.gif");
	+ background-repeat:no-repeat; (repeat-x,repeat-y)
	+ background-position: right top;
	+ background-attachment: scrolled; (fixed)


Border:
	+border-style: solid;	(dotted)
	+border-width: medium;	(thick, *px)
	+border-color: blue;
	+border sides:
		+border-top-style: dotted;
		+border-right-style: solid;
		+border-bottom-style: dotted;
		+border-left-style: solid;
	+margin: top right bottom left;
	+Padding:		
	    + padding-top
	    + padding-right
	    + padding-bottom
	    + padding-left
	+Font family:
		+font-style: normal; (italic, oblique)
		+font-weight: normal;
		+font-variant: normal;(small-caps)
		

To move the image which inside another element to the center:
	position: absolute;
	left:50%;                                    //50% of the background element;
	transform: translate(-50%);    				 //50% of the image itself;